In this press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discusses various topics. She announces that President Trump will be traveling to Indianapolis to deliver remarks on tax cuts and reforms. Sanders also mentions that the President will sign a presidential memorandum to promote STEM education in American schools. She defends the President's stance on NFL players kneeling during the national anthem, stating that it is about honoring the flag and the men and women who fought for it. Sanders addresses the issue of North Korea's foreign minister claiming that President Trump declared war on North Korea, stating that it is absurd and that the US has not declared war. She also discusses other topics such as Secretary Price's use of private jets, the administration's response to Hurricane Maria in Puerto Rico, and upcoming refugee and tax reform announcements.